SÉNÉGAL 🇸🇳 Eat the World NYC review: At both locations of Le Baobab Gouygui (the first is in Harlem), I had only ever been for lunch service, which offers a few rotating daily selections. Dinner service opens up quite a few new options, including these three jaw-droppers. So far, not a dish from this franchise has disappointed, the chefs are doing Senegalese food right. Particularly delicious were the plates of grilled lamb known as dibi (debe here), and the chicken brochettes, both covered with the signature onions and mustard relish. The full story from 2106 updated on our website.
